SIMPLE: luminous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Luminous
<hw>Lu"mi*nous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>luminosus</ets>, fr. <ets>lumen</ets> light: cf. F.
<ets>lumineux</ets>. See <er>Luminary</er>,
<er>Illuminate</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Shining; emitting or reflecting light; brilliant;
bright; <as>as, the is a <ex>luminous</ex> body; a <ex>luminous</ex>
color.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Fire burneth wood, making it . . . <qex>luminous</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The mountains lift . . . their lofty and <qex>luminous</qex>
heads.</q> <rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Illuminated; full of light; bright; <as>as, many
candles made the room <ex>luminous</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Up the staircase moved a <qex>luminous</qex> space in the
darkness.</q> <rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Enlightened; intelligent; also, clear; intelligible;
<as>as, a <ex>luminous</ex> mind</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧ <xex>Luminous</xex>
eloquence.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Macaulay.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧ A <xex>luminous</xex>
statement.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Brougham.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Luminous paint</b></col>, <cd>a paint made up with some
phosphorescent substance, as sulphide of calcium, which after exposure
to a strong light is luminous in the dark for a time.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Lucid; clear; shining; perspicuous.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Lu"mi*nous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Lu"mi*nous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>luminousness</ent>⟦br⟧
